description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a dietitian with a passion for gastroenterology to work in St Marks Hospital. St Mark’s is a national centre for intestinal failure and gastroenterology and the dietitians are an established and valued part of the MDT. The service has recently been split onto 2 sites, with some services remaining at Northwick Park Hospital and other services at Central Middlesex Hospital. You will be based at Central Middlesex Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will cover a caseload of patients on the inpatient colorectal surgery &amp; intestinal rehabilitation wards and you will work within the hospitals parenteral nutrition team. You will also cover a weekly Gastroenterology Clinic and support the IBD specialist dietitian. The St Marks dietetic team includes 6 other experienced dietitians and is a cohesive, supportive team. Regular evidence based groups and breakfast clubs support the development of clinical skills and teamwork. You will be able to actively participate in developing the service both clinically and strategically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate would have strong gastroenterology and parenteral nutrition experience. A proactive approach and good time management skills are also key is in this busy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The St Marks dietitians sit within the wider dietetic team of acute and community dietitians based at Northwick Park &amp; Ealing Hospitals. This large department offers many opportunities for learning and development due to the range of specialities. The department is committed to Continuing Professional Development, and we have an established clinical governance programme including evidence based clinical groups, audit, clinical supervision and critical appraisal. We are a well-established student trainer and the post will involve supervision of students in the clinical area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Mina Bharal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Acute Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: m.bharal@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 020 8 8692666&lt;/p&gt;
